description: Reserved matters application for Phase 9.1 of the Acton Gardens masterplan detailing Landscaping, Appearance, Scale, Access and Layout in relation to the construction of one apartment building varying between four-storeys and six-storeys in height and containing 68 new residential units (18 x 1 bedroom, 37 x 2 bedroom and 13 x 3 bedroom); associated private and semi-private amenity space, refuse/recycling and bicycle storage; plant rooms, car parking; loading area; works to the public highway and public realm improvements, following the demolition of Webb Court and Bennet Court and tree removal; application made part pursuant to conditions 2 (Reserved Matters) and 4 (Reserved Matters) of outline planning permission reference P/2012/0708 dated 13/08/2013 (amended by minor material amendment application PP/2014/2142 dated 21/07/2014, PP/2014/6303 dated 31/03/15 and 160794VAR dated  09/12/2016)
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.
Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).
| The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans and documents:

Design and Access Statement, prepared by Allies and Morrison, dated August 2017; Design and Access Addendum 1, prepared by Allies and Morrison dated November 2017; Sustainability Statement, prepared by Hodkinson, dated August 2017; Daylight and Sunlight Report, prepared by GL Hearn, dated 11th August 2017; Arboricultural Report & Tree Condition Survey, ref: 0717-2141-JGS, prepared by Ruskins, dated August 2017; Planning Statement, prepared by Barton Willmore, dated August 2017; Cover Letter, prepared by Barton Willmore, dated 14th August 2017; Transport Statement, ref: PH/MD/JN/WH/ITL13056-001B, prepared by i-Transport LLP,                                                                                           dated 11th August 2017; Energy Statement, prepared by Hodkinson, dated August 2017; 16250_00_07_001 Rev P1; 16250_00_07_002 Rev P1; 16250_00_07_003 Rev P2; 16250_01_07_151-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_100-Rev-P4; 16250_01_07_101-Rev-P2; 16250_01_07_102-Rev-P2; 16250_01_07_103-Rev-P2; 16250_01_07_200-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_202-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_203-Rev-P2; 16250_01_07_204-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_205-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_302-Rev-P1; 16250_01_07_303-Rev-P1; Note, ref: 16250_01, Secured by Design, prepared by Allies and Morrison, dated 18/09/2017; 10007_PLN_001-V11 and TPP-01-Rev-2 as prepared by LUC.

Technical Note, Ref: PH/MD/ITL13056-003ATN, Transport Statement Addendum, prepared by i-Transport LLP, dated 29/09/17; Residential Travel Plan Acton Gardens Phase 9.1, ref: PH/MD/ITL13056-002D-R, prepared by i-Transport LLP, dated 19/10/2017. ITL13056-SK-001 Rev I.
Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning.

| The approved development in Phase 9.1, shall incorporate the mitigation measures including the internal blinds to all residential units to reduce the risk of overheating in accordance with the approved Energy Statement V3 dated 11/08/2017 and Dynamic Overheating Assessment v.2 dated 10/08/2017 both prepared by Hodkinson Consultancy. The mitigation measures shall follow the Mayor's Cooling Hierarchy and comply with CIBSE TM52 and TM49 criteria.

Reason: To ensure that the development is energy efficient and takes steps to reduce the risk of overheating, while reducing the need for active cooling, improve ventilation and daylighting, in accordance with policies 5.2, 5.3 and 5.9 of the London Plan (2016).

| The 120 No. on-site cycle parking facilities shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details and shall be completed and made available for use prior to first occupation of the dwellings hereby approved and be retained for such use thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that there is adequate provision for cycle parking within the site in accordance with policies 1.1, 1.2 & 2.1 of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 Development Plan Document (2012); policy 6.13 of the adopted Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013); policies 6.9 & 6.13 of The London Plan (2016), and The National Planning Policy Framework (2012).

| Samples of all external materials shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of works of the relevant part.  The development shall be constructed in accordance with the approved materials and be retained as such, thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings in accordance with policies 1.1(h) and 2.1(c) of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 Development Plan Document (2012); policy 7.6 of the London Plan (2016) and policy 7B of the adopted Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013).

| Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved no work shall commence on the relevant part until further details of the proposed play space shall be submitted in writing to and approved by the local planning authority, Ealing Council.  Such details shall thereafter be implemented in accordance with those approved details and be thereby retained.

Reason: To secure an inclusive, safe and high quality built environment for all users of the site and be sustainable.  In accordance with policies 3.5, 3.6, 7.2 and 7.6 of the London Plan 2016 and policies 1.1(e) and 1.1(i) of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 Development Plan Document (2012).

| The details of hard and soft landscaping including the tree protection and tree planting proposals as submitted to and hereby approved by the local planning authority shall be laid out and planted prior to the occupation of the development.  Any trees or plants which within 5 years of planting, die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased shall be replaced with others of the same size and species and in the same positions within the next planting season.  The landscaping shall thereafter be maintained permanently.
Reason: To ensure that the development is landscaped in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies 7.19 and 7.21 of the London Plan 2016.

| All of the car parking facilities including two parking spaces to be provided with electric charging points and a further two spaces to have passive provision for future electric charging points and the associated access and manoeuvring areas shall be implemented and brought into use prior to first occupation, and these areas shall not thereafter be obstructed or used for any other purpose.

Reason: To ensure that the development accords with Policies 6.13 and 7.2 of the London Plan, 2016 and Policies 1.1(h) and 1.2(k) of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 Development Plan Document, 2012.
| The refuse and recycling storage enclosures hereby approved shall be fully implemented and made available for use prior to first occupation of the development and retained thereafter.

Reason: In the interests of the adequate disposal, storage and collection of waste and recycling, to protect the living conditions of occupiers of the area and in the interests of highway and pedestrian safety all in accordance with Policies 1.1, 1.2 & 3.8 of the adopted Ealing Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 Development Plan Document (2012); Policies 3.5, 7A, & 7B of the adopted Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013); Policies 5.16, 6.3 & 7.15 of the London Plan (2016), and the National Planning Policy Framework (2012).
